      "text": "Unveiling the Secrets of Functional Genomics Introduction to Functional Genomics: Unraveling the Mysteries of the Genome Functional genomics, a field that has revolutionized our understanding of the intricate relationships between genes, environment, and phenotype, is an area of research that seeks to understand the functions and interactions of genes and proteins.",
